An Ibadan chief, Oloye Adegboyega Adegoke, has joined the Oyo South senatorial district race ahead of the 2023 general elections. Adegoke, who is the Aare-Onibon Balogun of Ibadan land, said that he will be contesting the election on the platform of All Progressives Congress (APC). He made these disclosures on Friday while inaugurating his contact and mobilization teams. Our correspondent gathered that Oyo South senatorial district consists of nine local government areas. The local government areas are; Ibadan North, Ibadan North East, Ibadan North West, Ibadan South East, Ibadan South West, Ibarapa Central, Ibarapa East, Ibarapa North and Ido Local Government Areas. Adegoke, while speaking, insisted that the senatorial district deserved better representation. He described the senatorial district as the nucleus of the state. He maintained that his aspiration was borne out of service to the people of the senatorial district and the state as a whole. Adegoke said, “Oyo South is the nucleus of Oyo State and there is a lot which a competent person representing the district at the red chamber could offer to improve the fortune of the district and the state as whole. “I want to implore all of us to always abide by the principle of all-inclusiveness and politics without violence or bitterness but politics of objectivity and constructive in all steps taken to reach the promised land. “I want to enjoin you all to remain steadfast, remain committed to this course at the end of the day, victory shall be ours.”